3/ped.xml:[&lt;b&gt;radh&lt;/b&gt; or &lt;b&gt;randh&lt;/b&gt;, differentiated in Pāli to 2 meanings &amp; 2 verbs according to Dhtm: "hiŋsāyaŋ" (148), and "pāke" (827). In the former sense given as raṇḍ, in the latter &lt;b&gt;randh&lt;/b&gt;. The root is freq. in the Vedas, in meaning 1. It belongs perhaps to Ags. rendan to rend: see Walde, &lt;i&gt;Lat. Wtb.&lt;/i&gt; s, v. lumbus]
