3/ped.xml:[Vedic vṛkṣa. See Geiger, &lt;i&gt;P.Gr.&lt;/i&gt; § 13, with note. Pischel, &lt;i&gt;Prk. Gr.&lt;/i&gt; § 320 puts rukkha to Sk. &lt;b&gt;rukṣa&lt;/b&gt; (shining which as Pischel, following Roth. says has also the meaning "tree" in Ṛgveda). The Prk. form is rukkha Cp. Wackernagel, &lt;i&gt;Altind. Gr.&lt;/i&gt; 1, § 184 b. We find a byform &lt;b&gt;rakkha&lt;/b&gt; at J &lt;smallcaps&gt;iii.&lt;/smallcaps&gt;144. Cp. &lt;i&gt;Brethren,&lt;/i&gt; pp. 185, 416 where the B&lt;sup&gt;n&lt;/sup&gt; MS. has rukkha kathā the meaning being rakkha˚]
