4/ped.xml:[cp. Vedic harṣate Idg. &lt;b&gt;*ĝher&lt;/b&gt; to bristle (of hair), as in Lat. horreo ("horrid, horripilation"), ēr hedgehog ("bristler")=Gr. &lt;at&gt;xh/r&lt;/at&gt; id.; Lat. hirtus, hispidus "rough"; Ags. gorst=gorse; Ger. granne &amp; many others, for which see Walde, ;&lt;i&gt;Lat. Wtb.&lt;/i&gt; s. v. ēr. -- The Dhtp (309) defines as "tuṭṭhi." See also ghaŋsati&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; pahaŋsati&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;, pahaṭṭha&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;, pahaŋsita&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;]
